This paper deals with unsupervised image-to-image translation, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and cycle-consistent loss, which are common techniques in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the Cityscapes dataset, which is a popular dataset for semantic segmentation (cs.GR). Finally, the experiments involve multiple datasets, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
